'''GIGAS -OLYMPUS-''' is a cross-platform, asymmetrical PvP game in which a giant VR player battles against many smaller 'human' players. The GIGA (gigantic VR player) is given many bombs and unique weapons to fight against these small players.{{Infobox/World|name=GIGAS -OLYMPUS-|image=GIGAS-OLYMPUS-thumbnail.png|author=キャンディちゃん|capacity=32 (32)|platforms=PC, Android|tags=game, pvp, quest, battle|languages=English, Japanese|id=wrld_69c41e95-1539-426a-a321-34412e0b021e|published=Feb 18 2025}}

== GIGAS ==
The GIGA is the gigantic VR player in a match. The GIGA is selected from the list of reserved seats in the lobby, in order of the first person to reserve a seat to be the GIGA, to the last. When the match begins, the GIGA is on the opposite side of the field as the human players, with many weapons surrounding them. These weapons consist of 4 normal bombs (exploding a few seconds after they're thrown), 2 slowing bombs (exploding into a pool on the ground that slows players), and other unique weapons depending on the loadout that the GIGA chooses before the game starts. The goal is to defeat enough players before the players score too many points by running across the field and jumping on the buttons below the GIGA. 

== Human players ==
The human players, are everybody other than the GIGA in a match, spawning on the opposite side if the field in an elevated position, as not to get spawn killed. The goal is to deal enough damage to the GIGA before the GIGA kills too many players, in order to gain points, players must run towards the GIGA and bounce on pads directly in front of them. Hitting the pads bounces the player to a separate platform with a turret, allowing the player to shoot the turret and deal damage to the GIGA. The player must jump from the platform and bounce on a pad again before they can fire another turret.

